  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">.NET 8 Minimal API + BackgroundService. Middleware is registered in the BFF pipeline; runs on every authenticated request.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Audit is NOT a substitute for authorization. The endpoint filters (ADR-008) gate access; audit records the access AFTER authorization passes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI registration via `AddActionEngineModule()` extension. Module total ≤15 non-framework registrations.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Audit fields enrichment for Action Engine concerns. Tool dispatch audit is written by `IToolHandlerRegistry` (task 026 choke point); this middleware extension enriches the request scope. The audit emission path does NOT create new CRUD→AI dependencies.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">**PRIMARY**. Tier 2 hash-only audit entries (no Tool content). Tier 3 Cosmos work history, tenant-partitioned, GDPR erasure path. MUST send minimum text required to achieve outcome. MUST log only identifiers, sizes, timings, outcome codes. MUST scope all persisted AI artifacts by tenant. MUST NOT log document contents, prompts, or model responses verbatim. MUST NOT store verbatim AI response in Tier 2 audit (hash only).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">If the middleware emits errors (e.g., audit-sink unavailable), it does NOT block the request — fails open with telemetry. The audit sink failure is logged but does not bubble to the caller as a request failure.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">No new NuGet packages without budget verification. Cosmos client + AuditHashHelper already in module.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge checklist: placement = BFF, publish-size delta verified, no new HIGH-severity CVE.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">G6 acceptance gate: Every Tool dispatch writes audit (ADR-015 Tier 2 + Tier 3) — verified by audit middleware integration test (G6).</constraint>
  </constraints>

