  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm working tree clean, branch is `work/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1`, baseline build passes. Confirm tasks 026 (IToolHandlerRegistry) and 041 (orchestrator) show ✅ in TASK-INDEX.md. Read the existing `AuditEnrichmentMiddleware.cs` + `AuditEntry.cs` + `AuditLogService.cs` + `AuditHashHelper.cs` to capture current shape. (task-execute Step 0)</step>
    <step order="1">Load `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` and answer the pre-merge checklist in `notes/decisions/task-043-bff-extensions-checklist.md`. Cite placement = BFF (spec.md §6).</step>
    <step order="2">Determine `IActionExecutionContextAccessor` status: if task 041 added it, reuse. If not, create `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/IActionExecutionContextAccessor.cs` + `ActionExecutionContextAccessor.cs` using `AsyncLocal&lt;ActionExecutionContext&gt;` (same pattern as `HttpContextAccessor`). Register as `Singleton` in DI. The orchestrator (task 041) sets the context at run start; the middleware reads it during scope enrichment.</step>
    <step order="3">Edit `AuditEnrichmentMiddleware.cs`: in the existing `BeginScope` dictionary, ADD the Action-Engine fields conditionally — `if (actionContextAccessor.Current is { } ctx)` populate `actionId`, `runId`, `toolId`, `phase`, `gateDecision`. Inject `IActionExecutionContextAccessor` via constructor (singleton-safe). For non-AE requests, the accessor's `Current` is null and the fields are omitted — non-AE requests unaffected.</step>
    <step order="4">Edit `AuditEntry.cs`: add fields `ActionId`, `RunId`, `ToolId`, `Phase`, `GateDecision`, `ContentHash` (string — SHA-256 hex), `TenantId` (string, mandatory for Tier 3 partition). Mark `TenantId` as required in JSON serialization.</step>
    <step order="5">Edit `AuditLogService.cs` + `IAuditLogService.cs`: extend `WriteAsync` (or add `WriteToolDispatchAsync(AuditEntry, ct)`) to emit two-tier: (a) Tier 2 entry to existing audit sink (logger or whatever the current sink is) — hash-only, NO Tool content; (b) Tier 3 entry to Cosmos `work-history` container with partition key = `tenantId`. Add `DeleteWorkHistoryForTenantAsync(string tenantId, CancellationToken ct)` for GDPR erasure — deletes all Cosmos documents in the `tenantId` partition.</step>
    <step order="6">Use `AuditHashHelper.cs` (existing) to compute `ContentHash` over Tool input + output blobs. The orchestrator (task 041) and `IToolHandlerRegistry` (task 026) call the audit service with the raw blob; the audit service hashes and stores ONLY the hash in Tier 2. Tier 3 also stores the hash, NEVER the raw content (ADR-015 binding).</step>
    <step order="7">DI registration: register `IActionExecutionContextAccessor` as Singleton in `AddActionEngineModule()`. The audit-service additions reuse existing DI. Confirm total non-framework registrations ≤15 (ADR-010).</step>
    <step order="8">Write the **G6 integration test** at `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/ActionEngine/AuditEnrichmentIntegrationTests.cs`: dispatch a Tool through the orchestrator (which calls `IToolHandlerRegistry` which writes audit); assert (a) a Tier 2 audit entry exists with `ActionId`, `RunId`, `ToolId`, `Phase`, `ContentHash` populated; (b) a Tier 3 Cosmos document exists with partition key = the test tenant id; (c) NEITHER entry contains the raw Tool input or output (assert by inspection — only the hash is present); (d) `DeleteWorkHistoryForTenantAsync(testTenantId)` removes the Tier 3 entry while leaving entries for other tenants untouched.</step>
    <step order="9">Verify GDPR erasure end-to-end: seed Cosmos with entries for two tenants (test-tenant-A, test-tenant-B), call `DeleteWorkHistoryForTenantAsync("test-tenant-A")`, assert only tenant A's entries are deleted, tenant B's remain.</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates per task-execute Step 9.5: `code-review` on the middleware edit + audit service edit + new accessor; `adr-check` verifies ADR-008 (audit is post-authz), ADR-013 (no new CRUD→AI deps), ADR-015 (Tier 2 hash + Tier 3 Cosmos tenant-partitioned + GDPR erasure + no verbatim content), ADR-019 (audit sink failure does not bubble as request error), ADR-029 (no new packages). Re-run `dotnet build` and integration tests.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 043 ✅. Verify it unblocks tasks 060 (integration tests phase), 061, 062, 063. Reset `current-task.md` for the next active task.</step>
    <step order="11">Document any deviations from this plan in `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/task-043-handoff.md` and add a brief commit message recap.</step>
  </steps>

